headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored nine points in the final 1:24, including the go-ahead 3-pointer with 14.5 seconds on the clock, lifting the Miami Heat to a 107-104 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Terry Rozier's go-ahead 3-pointer with 14.5 seconds left helps the Heat beat the Cavaliers 107-104

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points and eight rebounds, Tyrese Haliburton added 20 points and nine assists, and the Indiana Pacers routed the short-handed Detroit Pistons 122-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Haliburton combine for 45 points as Pacers rout short-handed Pistons 122-103

headlines.description: — Milwaukee Bucks guard Patrick Beverley made a spin move in the lane, floated a jumper over Boston's Luke Kornet and then headed back on defense in a crouch, holding his hand a few inches above the floor to mock the Celtics center.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics open big lead, hold on to beat Bucks without Giannis, 122-119

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 13 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists for his NBA-leading 24th triple-double of the season, De’Aaron Fox scored 20 points and the Sacramento Kings routed the short-handed Raptors 123-89 on Wednesday night, extending Toronto’s...
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has 24th triple-double as Kings rout short-handed Raptors 123-89

events.name: Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Chet Holmgren scored 35 points and tied a career high with 14 rebounds and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the short-handed Utah Jazz 119-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chet Holmgren scores 35, grabs 14 rebounds and Thunder beat Jazz 119-107

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors received a halftime message about taking control of the third quarter and making regular defensive stops, and they wasted no time stealing the momentum once back on the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry reaches 300 3-pointers for record fifth time, Warriors beat Grizzlies 137-116

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen scored 32 points and tied a career high with nine 3-pointers, leading the Phoenix Suns past the Philadelphia 76ers 115-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grayson Allen scores 32, ties career high with 9 3-pointers, Suns beat sliding Sixers 115-102

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 27 points, James Harden had 19 points and 14 assists and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Portland Trail Blazers 116-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George and Harden lead Clippers past Trail Blazers 116-103
